==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muskellunge
<hw>Mus"kel*lunge</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From the Amer.
Indian name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large American pike
(<spn>Esox masquinongy</spn> formerly <spn>Esox nobilior</spn>) found in
the Great Lakes, and other Northern lakes, and in the St. Lawrence
River. It is valued as a food fish.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>maskallonge</asp>, <asp>maskalonge</asp>, <asp>maskinonge</asp>,
<asp>muskallonge</asp>, <asp>muskellonge</asp>, and
<asp>muskelunjeh</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Musket</ent>⟦br⟧
